already succumbed to his injuries.Speaking to
Daily Sun, Primrose Police Station Sergeant Styles Maome confirmed that an
inquest docket has been opened.“The granny
was about to leave the house with the baby,” he said.“She put
the child on car seat. While she was about to open the door, the family dog
attacked the child and mauled the child on the head. The child died on the
scene. An inquest docket was opened for investigation. “The granny
was taken to hospital to be treated for shock, he also said.ER24’s
Russel Meiring said: “Paramedics were let into a lounge of a home where they
found the body of a child.“We
immediately assessed the boy and saw that he had sustained several serious bite
wounds and showed no signs of life. Nothing more could be done for him and he
was declared dead.”